{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T13:59:52.905Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The memory hierarchy in Claude Code is the layered system that determines "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files and rules are loaded, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"in what order"},{"type":"text","text":", and with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"what priority"},{"type":"text","text":" — so that the most contextually relevant and specific instructions shape Claude's behavior without flooding the context window."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the memory hierarchy as concentric rings of authority, from widest scope to narrowest. Each ring adds instructions to Claude's context window at session start, layered on top of the previous one. The outermost ring (organization-wide policy) is always present; the innermost ring (your per-project local file) is the last thing Claude reads, giving it the highest contextual weight."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key principle: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"all discovered files are concatenated, not overridden"},{"type":"text","text":". Nothing is silently ignored unless you explicitly exclude it. Instructions from broader scopes stack with instructions from narrower scopes."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Four-Level Scope Hierarchy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude Code defines four distinct scopes for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files, loaded in this order at session start — from broadest to most specific:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Level"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"File Location"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Purpose"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Who Controls It"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared With"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Managed Policy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/Library/Application Support/ClaudeCode/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":"; Linux/WSL: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/etc/claude-code/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":"; Windows: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"C:\\Program Files\\ClaudeCode\\CLAUDE.md"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Org-wide standards, compliance, security"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"IT/DevOps via MDM/Ansible"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All users on the machine"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. User"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/CLAUDE.md"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Personal preferences across all projects"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You only (all projects)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Project"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"./CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"./.claude/CLAUDE.md"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team-shared project conventions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team via source control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All team members"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Local"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"./CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" (add to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".gitignore"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Private per-project notes"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You only (current project)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Within each directory encountered during the walk, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" is always appended "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":", so your personal notes at a given level are the last thing Claude reads at that level."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Directory Tree Walking: How Files Actually Load"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you launch Claude Code in a directory (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"foo/bar/"},{"type":"text","text":"), Claude walks "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"up"},{"type":"text","text":" the directory tree from your working directory toward the filesystem root, collecting "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" at every level it encounters. For "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"foo/bar/"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"foo/bar/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — found and collected"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"foo/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — found and collected"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — user-level, collected"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/etc/claude-code/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — managed policy, collected"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"These files are then "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"concatenated into context in reverse order"},{"type":"text","text":" — from the filesystem root down to your working directory. So the actual injection order into Claude's context is:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"/etc/claude-code/CLAUDE.md       ← Loaded first (least specific)\n~/.claude/CLAUDE.md\nfoo/CLAUDE.md\nfoo/bar/CLAUDE.md                ← Loaded last (most specific)\nfoo/bar/CLAUDE.local.md          ← Very last at this level"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This means more specific instructions are read "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"last"},{"type":"text","text":", giving them the highest contextual prominence — exactly analogous to how CSS specificity or Python's MRO resolves conflicts."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subdirectory Files: Lazy Loading"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files located in subdirectories "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"below"},{"type":"text","text":" your working directory are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"not"},{"type":"text","text":" loaded at session start. They are loaded lazily — only when Claude reads a file inside that subdirectory during the session. This is a deliberate design decision: a monorepo might have dozens of nested "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files, and loading all of them upfront would flood the context window. Only the files relevant to the current task's files are ever injected."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This also has an important implication for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/compact"},{"type":"text","text":": project-root "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files survive compaction (Claude re-reads them from disk after compacting), but nested subdirectory "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files do "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"not"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically re-inject — they reload only the next time Claude reads a file in that subdirectory."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"},{"type":"text","text":": Modular Rule Files"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For larger projects, you can further subdivide instructions beyond a monolithic "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" using the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"},{"type":"text","text":" directory. All "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".md"},{"type":"text","text":" files in this directory are discovered recursively, so you can organize by team, feature area, or concern:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"your-project/\n├── .claude/\n│   ├── CLAUDE.md\n│   └── rules/\n│       ├── code-style.md       # Always loaded\n│       ├── testing.md          # Always loaded\n│       ├── frontend/\n│       │   └── react.md        # Always loaded\n│       └── api-rules.md        # Path-scoped (only when Claude reads API files)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules without "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"paths"},{"type":"text","text":" frontmatter load at session start with the same priority as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":". Rules "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"with"},{"type":"text","text":" a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"paths"},{"type":"text","text":" frontmatter field load conditionally — only when Claude reads a file matching the specified glob pattern:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"markdown"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\npaths:\n  - \"src/api/**/*.ts\"\n---\n\n# API Development Rules\n- All endpoints must include input validation\n- Use the standard error response format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This path-scoped conditional loading is the primary tool for keeping context lean on large codebases. TypeScript API rules only enter the context window when Claude is actually working with TypeScript API files."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto Memory: Claude's Own Layer"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Alongside the human-authored "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy sits a separate memory layer that Claude writes itself — stored at "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/projects/<project>/memory/MEMORY.md"},{"type":"text","text":". This is not part of the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy, but it is loaded at every session start (first 200 lines or 25KB, whichever comes first)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key distinction from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files are loaded "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"in full"},{"type":"text","text":" regardless of length (though shorter produces better adherence)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"MEMORY.md"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"truncated"},{"type":"text","text":" at 200 lines / 25KB at session start; detail is offloaded into topic files ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"debugging.md"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"api-conventions.md"},{"type":"text","text":") that Claude reads on demand"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All worktrees and subdirectories within the same git repository share a single auto memory directory, since the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<project>"},{"type":"text","text":" path is derived from the git repository root — not the specific subdirectory you launched Claude from."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Load-Order Priority Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Putting it all together, the effective load order from first-loaded (lowest contextual weight) to last-loaded (highest contextual weight) is:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Managed policy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — always present, cannot be excluded"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"User"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — your personal cross-project preferences"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"User-level rules"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/rules/*.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — your personal rule files"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ancestor project"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files — walking up from working directory to repo root"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Working directory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" / "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — project instructions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/*.md"},{"type":"text","text":" without "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"paths"},{"type":"text","text":" — unconditional project rules"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Working directory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — your private local notes (last at this level)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Path-scoped rules"},{"type":"text","text":" — injected on demand when matching files are read"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Subdirectory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files — lazy-loaded when Claude reads files there"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto memory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"MEMORY.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — Claude's own notes, first 200 lines / 25KB"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exclusions: Filtering the Hierarchy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In large monorepos, ancestor "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files from other teams may be irrelevant to your work. The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"claudeMdExcludes"},{"type":"text","text":" setting in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/settings.local.json"},{"type":"text","text":" lets you skip specific files by glob pattern:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"claudeMdExcludes\": [\n    \"**/other-team/CLAUDE.md\",\n    \"/home/user/monorepo/other-team/.claude/rules/**\"\n  ]\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Patterns match against absolute file paths and merge across settings layers (user, project, local, managed). However, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"managed policy "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" files cannot be excluded"},{"type":"text","text":" — this ensures organization-wide instructions always apply."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The hierarchy has four scope levels: managed policy → user → project → local. All matching files are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"concatenated"},{"type":"text","text":" in that order; more specific files are read last and carry higher contextual weight."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude walks up the directory tree from your working directory, collecting all "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files it encounters along the way."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subdirectory "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files below your working directory are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"lazily loaded"},{"type":"text","text":" on demand, not at session start — this keeps context lean."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"},{"type":"text","text":" files add a modular layer; use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"paths"},{"type":"text","text":" frontmatter to make rules "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"conditional"},{"type":"text","text":" on file type, preventing irrelevant instructions from consuming context tokens."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto memory ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"MEMORY.md"},{"type":"text","text":") is a parallel layer Claude writes itself, subject to a 200-line / 25KB load cap, with detailed notes offloaded to on-demand topic files."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"claudeMdExcludes"},{"type":"text","text":" to filter out irrelevant ancestor files in monorepos; managed policy files are the only layer that cannot be excluded."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
